[{"type":"heading","level":2,"children":[{"text":"Session Summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Project: Pilot Mastery Academy | Date: 2026-04-11 | Messages: 245"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"children":[{"text":"Conversation Excerpt"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"children":[{"text":"🧑 You"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"build all of this into https://github.com/rtmendes/pilot-mastery-academy.git Canonical doc (in repo)\nUse this file as the single mission spec (it’s also required by CI now):"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"instructions/09_FULL_STACK_CONNECT_CLAUDE_CODE.md\nIt’s linked from instructions/00_MAIN_BUILD_INSTRUCTION.md. Committed as be75ebc."}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Paste this into Claude Code (system / first message)\nYou are connecting the Pilot Mastery Academy monorepo to GitHub, Vercel, and Stripe so the web app in `platform/` is live and checkout works end-to-end.\nMUST READ FIRST (open in context):\n- instructions/09_FULL_STACK_CONNECT_CLAUDE_CODE.md  (primary checklist — follow in order)\n- platform/README.md\n- platform/.env.example\n- platform/vercel.json\n- platform/api/ (all serverless handlers)\n- automation/api-specs.md (Stripe metadata convent"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"children":[{"text":"🤖 Claude"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Let me start by reading the key instruction files and understanding the current state of the repo."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"children":[{"text":"🤖 Claude"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Good — I've read all the key files. The codebase is well-structured: serverless API handlers in `platform/api/`, a clean `vercel.json`, and proper billing/client-url libs. Let me set up tracking and start working through the checklist."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"children":[{"text":"🤖 Claude"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\n**Monorepo deploy pattern**: This project uses a common monorepo pattern where the deployable app (`platform/`) is a subdirectory. Vercel's \"Root Directory\" setting is critical — it tells Vercel to `cd platform/` before running `npm install` and `npm run build`. The `vercel.json` inside `platform/` controls build commands, output directory, SPA rewrites, and function config. Without setting Root Directory correctly, Vercel would try to build from repo root and fail."}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"**Serverless API design**: The `api/` folder uses Vercel's file-based routing convention — each `.ts` file becomes an endpoint (e.g., `api/health.ts` → `GET /api/health`). The webhook handler at `api/webhooks/stripe.ts` disables body parsing (`config.api.bodyParser = false`) be"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"children":[{"text":"🤖 Claude"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Branch tracking is missing (no `[origin/main]` shown). Let me fix that and then start the local build validation in parallel."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"children":[{"text":"🤖 Claude"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Upstream tracking is set. Local `main` is at `be75ebc` which matches `origin/main` — nothing to push."}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"... and 239 more messages in this session."}]}]
